An optimized version of openQCD-1.2 for Intel processors with 512 bit vector width
==================================================================================

DESCRIPTION

   This patch implements the Dirac operators with intel Intrincic operations in
   order to use the full vector width on Intel Skylake, Knight Landing and other
   processors. 

   To enable the optimized version add -DAVX512 to the compiler flags.

AUTHORS

   This patch extends the openQCD code written by Martin Luscher, Stefan
   Schaefer and other contributors (see http://luscher.web.cern.ch/luscher/openQCD/).
   
   The batch has been written by and tested by Jarno Rantaharju and Michele Messiti.

